 l is IU's yearly celebration of student-produced films. Submitted films a
 re viewed and judged by IU alumni and awarded in several categories\, inc
 luding Best in Show\, Best Cinematography\, and Best Acting or Performanc
 e. Montage is a collaboration between IU Cinema and The Media School.</p>
 <p>  The collective runtime of the films is 90 minutes.</p><p><strong>Bon
 nie and Clyde</strong> (4 min) | Directed by Olivia Kinoshita</p><p>  A l
 esbian Bonnie and Clyde\, three vignettes follow their seemingly mundane 
 daily life: grocery shopping and cooking\, gardening\, and peaceful drive
 s. Each short feels like a romance until the chilling twist reveals they 
