SUMMARY:Sorry to Bother You | Granfalloon
DESCRIPTION:In an alternate present-day version of Oakland\, Calif.\, Bla
 ck telemarketer Cassius Green (LaKeith Stanfield) discovers a magical key
  to professional success. As Green's career begins to take off\, his frie
 nds and co-workers organize a protest against corporate oppression. Green
  soon falls under the spell of Steve Lift\, a cocaine-snorting CEO who of
 fers him a salary beyond his wildest dreams. Propelled into a macabre uni
 verse\, Green is forced to examine his conscience. Boots Riley's complete
 ly original\, bizarre\, and wildly prescient debut feature has plenty to 
 say about race\, class\, consumerism\, our media consumption\, and so muc
 h more. A phenomenal ensemble casts brings Riley's dystopian and witty vi
 sion to life\, including Tessa Thompson\, Steven Yeun\, and Danny Glover.
  [112 min\; comedy\, satire\, drama\, sci-fi\; English]
X-ALT-DESC;FMTTYPE=text/html:<p>  In an alternate present-day version of 
 Oakland\, Calif.\, Black telemarketer Cassius Green (LaKeith Stanfield) d
 iscovers a magical key to professional success. As Green's career begins 
 to take off\, his friends and co-workers organize a protest against corpo
 rate oppression. Green soon falls under the spell of Steve Lift\, a cocai
 ne-snorting CEO who offers him a salary beyond his wildest dreams. Propel
 led into a macabre universe\, Green is forced to examine his conscience. 
 Boots Riley's completely original\, bizarre\, and wildly prescient debut 
 feature has plenty to say about race\, class\, consumerism\, our media co
 nsumption\, and so much more. A phenomenal ensemble casts brings Riley's 
 dystopian and witty vision to life\, including Tessa Thompson\, Steven Ye
 un\, and Danny Glover. [112 min\; comedy\, satire\, drama\, sci-fi\; Engl
 ish]</p>
